The real issue is that many Americans are uncomfortable accepting the truth that their descendants came from Africa and were enslaved. Liberia was founded in the early 1800s by formerly enslaved Black Americans (often called Americo-Liberians) who were resettled from the United States, mainly through the American Colonization Society.
The first settlers arrived in 1822
Liberia declared independence in 1847
These settlers brought American culture with them: Christianity, Western clothing, English, U.S.-style government, and social structures
